08/07/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- European Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic met with Dutch diplomat Marnix Krop Wednesday (7 July) to discuss EU integration issues. 
Krop hailed Croatia's progress in implementing reforms, adding that the country's eventual accession would have a positive effect on the whole region.
In other news, members of parliament met on Wednesday with a delegation representing ethnic Croats living in Montenegro. 
The group is seeking help from Zagreb in resolving problems of high unemployment, a lack of funds for political and cultural activities, and the lengthy process involved in obtaining Croatian citizenship. 
(HINA, HRT - 07/07/04)
